Below are three Cloud Run Function examples showing how to trigger **Airflow**, **Dataflow**, and **Dataproc Serverless**. The first part of each function (receiving the Cloud Storage event, validating the CSV, etc.) is the same. Only the service invocation changes.

---

# 1. Cloud Run Function → Airflow

**Architecture**

```text
GCS
   │
Eventarc
   │
Cloud Run Function
   │
Airflow REST API
   │
Dataproc/Dataflow/Other Tasks
```

```python
import functions_framework
import requests
import google.auth
from google.auth.transport.requests import Request

AIRFLOW_URL = "https://<composer-url>/api/v1/dags/employee_dataproc_serverless/dagRuns"

@functions_framework.cloud_event
def trigger_airflow(cloud_event):

    data = cloud_event.data

    bucket = data["bucket"]
    file_name = data["name"]

    if not file_name.endswith(".csv"):
        return

    payload = {
        "conf": {
            "bucket": bucket,
            "file_path": file_name
        }
    }

    credentials, _ = google.auth.default()
    credentials.refresh(Request())

    headers = {
        "Authorization": f"Bearer {credentials.token}",
        "Content-Type": "application/json"
    }

    response = requests.post(
        AIRFLOW_URL,
        headers=headers,
        json=payload
    )

    response.raise_for_status()
```

